    ("T100", "Efforts (AdminUserActivity) -- T086 athlete-education strip pass", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "AdminUserActivity (the coach Efforts tab) was reworked AFTER the 2026-06-04 T086 sweep, so it never got the 'strip athlete-only explanatory copy from web coach mirrors' pass (flagged in T086 + T079 notes, never its own trackable task).",
     "DONE (no-op) -- 2026-06-08 audited AdminUserActivity.jsx end-to-end against the T086 rule. The post-T086 rebuild produced a data-only component: Strength/Cardio toggle, move cards (progress sparkline + 'Best ...' line + 'Last trained N days ago'), empty/loading states, and a functional Add-effort form whose only copy is field labels. NO attribution footers, motivational lines, how-to-log instructions, or explanatory subtitles remained -- nothing to strip. Closed without code change.",
     "web/src/pages/admin/tabs/AdminUserActivity.jsx (verified clean)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T101", "Client-detail view must reopen on the Dashboard tab, not the last-opened tab", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-07: open a client -> view a tab (e.g. Bodyweight) -> leave the client -> re-enter, and it reopens on the LAST tab (persisted, e.g. localStorage 'admin-user-tab-{id}' in AdminUserDetail). User wants it to ALWAYS reopen on the Dashboard tab. Fix: initialise activeTab='dashboard' on mount / stop restoring the persisted last-tab (AdminUserDetail + mirror in CoachClientDetail).",
     "DONE (admin side) 2026-06-07, committed 1390cf4, deployed index-BKgOlVxQ: AdminUserDetail activeTab now always inits to 'dashboard' (dropped the localStorage 'admin-user-tab-{id}' restore on mount); ?tab= URL deep-link still honored; handleTabChange no longer persists to localStorage. COACH side (CoachClientDetail.jsx) gets the same one-line fix as part of the T079 coach-reflection batch. REGRESSION FOLLOW-UP 2026-06-07 (committed 5040a0a / index-Cscsqrev): dropping the localStorage restore ALSO broke the move-detail back buttons -- they used to localStorage.setItem('admin-user-tab',activity)+navigate(bare client URL), which now lands on Dashboard. User: 'back from an effort detail should go to the Efforts page, not the dashboard.' Fixed AdminEffortDetail.goBack + AdminCardioDetail.onBack to navigate /admin/user/{id}?tab=activity (honored on mount); covers every strength/cardio sub-detail via the shared onBack prop.",
     "web AdminUserDetail.jsx (activeTab init + localStorage admin-user-tab-{id}); CoachClientDetail.jsx",
     "2026-06-07"),

    ("T102", "Redesign the client-detail profile header (control grouping + sizing)", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-07: the profile-summary card crammed every control into one undifferentiated right-side pill stack (status badges, coaching switcher, message, active toggle, settings, delete -- all same size, no grouping), and the snapshot stat badges ate a big centered full-width grid. User wanted: badges squished smaller + left-aligned; the pills sorted into labeled blocks by purpose; settings moved to the conventional top-right; Active relabeled to an account-status word; Intake Plan -> macro-plan set/not-set; a full makeover, not just reordering.",
     "DONE 2026-06-07 (committed afc2e7e / index-BbajJZEn): right side is now a settings GEAR (top-right, icon-only) over a 2x2 grid of labeled ControlGroups -- ACCOUNT (Active/Suspended toggle, relabeled from Active/Inactive), COACHING (the AthleteCoachingChip), PLAN (Macro plan set / No macro plan + Goal reached, relabeled from Intake Plan/Goal), MESSAGING (chat on/off + Message athlete). New ControlGroup helper (tiny uppercase caption over its controls). SnapshotBadge shrunk (rounded-full, px-2 py-0.5, text-[10px], no w-48%/min-h) + the badge row left-aligned (dropped justify-center). DELETE moved out of the header into the settings drawer's new 'Danger zone' slot (ClientSettingsDrawer gained a `dangerZone` prop; AdminUserDetail passes the Delete / Cancel-scheduled-deletion button, which closes the drawer then opens the existing confirm modal) -- mobile parity, per the user. Account status banners (suspended / scheduled-deletion / deleted) unchanged. Header row switched items-center -> items-start so the taller control column top-aligns. NOTE: this is the ADMIN view; the coach view (CoachClientDetail) gets it in the T079 coach-reflection batch. V2 REDESIGN 2026-06-07 (user rejected v1: 'too much empty space, titles literally saying what the pill already states'; asked how a modern app would do it from scratch, unconstrained by current pills/colors): replaced the labeled 2x2 ControlGroup grid with a record-header pattern (Linear/Stripe/Intercom style). Identity top-left; a single self-describing INLINE STATUS LINE under the email with NO captions (colored-dot Active/Suspended toggle, the coaching dropdown, 'Macro plan set'/'No macro plan' + 'Goal reached' as informative text, chat on/off toggle); and a right ACTION CLUSTER = primary lime Message button + Settings gear icon. Split by interaction type: informative text vs toggles vs open-panel actions (no redundant section titles, no empty grid). Removed the now-unused ControlGroup helper. Committed 318cb77 / index-36CFD12C. V3 TWEAKS 2026-06-07 (committed 3a1959a / index-DCKT1jNE, user feedback on v2): (1) Active + Chat status items now bordered pills so they read as clickable toggles (were borderless, 'didn't look like a button'); (2) faint '·' separators between status-line items; (3) macro-plan status is ONE mutually-exclusive state (corrected c50f7c9): goal reached -> 'Macro plan goal reached', else plan -> 'Macro plan set', else 'No macro plan' (never two together); (4) snapshot badges bigger (flex-1 + min-w-110 + px-2.5 py-1.5 text-[11px] rounded-lg) so they fill the bottom line edge-to-edge. MOBILE FIX 2026-06-07 (user: 'on mobile web the header looks awkward, line it up cleanly', committed 2b8d691 / index-DGlMypjR): the status line lived INSIDE the narrow name column (the action cluster ate the right side), so it wrapped awkwardly on mobile. Moved it to its OWN full-width row below the name (clean wrap on all widths); Message button collapses to icon-only on <sm (label shows at sm+); added shrink-0 to the action icons. Top row is now avatar + name/email + compact actions; status line spans full width underneath.",
     "web/src/pages/admin/AdminUserDetail.jsx (SnapshotBadge + ControlGroup + profile card); web/src/components/ClientSettingsDrawer.jsx (dangerZone slot)",
     "2026-06-07"),

    ("T103", "Admin client-settings mirror — admin edits a client's settings from the client detail page", "Coach/Admin", "Web+Mobile", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08: 'lets start working on the client detail settings page ... as an admin i need to access a clients details page to check on their settings as they set it and do any required changes ... it needs to mirror the client's exactly ... there could be things that as an admin i cant change ... this does not mirror on the coach, only admin can change client's settings.' AUDITED both ends via 2 parallel agents. CLIENT SETTINGS (mobile is source of truth; the live file is mobile/app/(app)/settings.tsx, NOT profile.tsx — renamed May 28 2026): 6 tabs Account/Preferences/Security/Connect/Billing/About. Account=photo/name/email/phone/dob/gender/delete. Preferences=units(weight/height/distance/fluid/date format)+body stats(weight/height/body_fat_band)+meal layout+enter-to-send. Security=privacy(share_online_status/share_last_seen)+biometric+app lock+change password. Connect=wearables. Billing=read-only txns. CLASSIFICATION -- admin CAN edit (DB-backed): photo,name,dob,gender,all units,body stats,body comp,meal layout,privacy toggles. CAN'T edit directly, needs client confirm (verification-gated): email(confirm link),phone(SMS OTP),password(needs current pw). CAN'T edit at all (device-local, lives on the phone): enter-to-send(AsyncStorage),biometric(SecureStore),app lock(AsyncStorage),wearable connects. CURRENT web tool = ClientSettingsDrawer (gear icon on AdminUserDetail) wrapping shared AccountSettings in target mode (targetUserId); narrow today — edits name/gender/dob/phone(plain)/weight/height + 4 unit prefs + 2 privacy toggles + 2 working support actions (send pw reset, send email link) + 2 stubs (disable biometric / sign out everywhere). USER DECISIONS 2026-06-08: (1) email=keep 'send the client a change link'. (2) phone=admin CHANGES the number + SENDS the client the OTP; the CLIENT enters it to verify (admin does NOT mark verified — sets number unverified, fires send-phone-otp to client's phone, client completes on their device). (3) device-local settings + wearables = OFF (don't show them at all) -> drops the Connect tab + the biometric/app-lock/enter-to-send rows; mirrored tabs become Account/Preferences/Security only. (4) BUILD NOW the 2 remote support actions (sign out everywhere = server-side session revoke; disable fingerprint everywhere = sets a flag, needs a mobile-side launch-check to actually clear on-device biometric). (5) MIRROR the client's exact tab structure. (6) BILLING = no billing page in settings; every transaction reflects to the ACTIVITY FEED instead (billing:* feed events already exist via trg_billing_event_to_activity — verify coverage, don't build a page). (7) COACH: coaches must NOT even have a client-settings button (none exists today; never add one; lock down the shared component so coach can't edit a client).",
     "PHASE 1 DONE 2026-06-08 (deploy index-BzP1EGVz.js, live hash verified). Cleanup + safety + bug fixes in AccountSettings.jsx: (a) COACH-LOCKDOWN safety -- change-password block was gated on `!isAdminMode`, so a coach editing a client (if ever wired) would see it and signInWithPassword/updateUser would silently change the COACH'S OWN password (updateUser acts on the JWT session user, not the target). Re-gated to `!isTargetMode` (self-only) -- so in ANY target mode (admin or coach) the password form is hidden; admin still gets the support actions (gated isAdminMode), coach-target gets nothing actionable. (b) TAB-POSITION bug -- the drawer shared the persisted-tab key 'myrx:settings_tab' with the admin's own /admin/profile AND had clearOnUnmount, so closing a client drawer wiped the admin's own tab choice; namespaced the drawer to 'myrx:settings_tab:client'. (c) SUPPORT-BUTTON lie -- sendPasswordReset/sendEmailChange never checked resetPasswordForEmail's {error}, showing 'Sent ✓' even on a failed/rate-limited send; now check error and render a 'Failed — try again' state (new 'error' branch in SupportActionRow). REMAINING PHASES (planned, not yet built): Phase 2 = mirror the editable settings (Account: add photo editing + phone set & 'send code to client' + keep email send-link; Preferences: add fluid unit + date format + body_fat_band picker [new web component] + meal-layout editor [reuse EditProfile's] + align swim to derive from distance like mobile; Security: keep privacy + email/pw send buttons). Phase 3 = verify billing txns flow to the activity feed (decision 6 — likely already via trg_billing_event_to_activity; fill gaps, NO billing page). Phase 4 = the 2 remote actions (sign-out-everywhere edge fn w/ service-role session revoke; disable-fingerprint flag via DB column + RPC). Phase 5 = mobile launch-check honoring the disable-fingerprint flag (clears SecureStore biometric + app lock). KNOWN GAP to resolve in Phase 2: the 'send email-change link' mechanism (resetPasswordForEmail -> /auth?mode=update-email) is unverified -- confirm /auth handles update-email mode or build a proper service-role email-change link. PHASE 2a (Preferences mirror) DONE 2026-06-08 (deploy index-DW_rUCDN.js, live verified; profiles columns fluid_unit/date_format/body_fat_band/swim_unit/meal_slots_default/phone_verified_at all confirmed via MCP): expanded the shared PreferencesTab so it mirrors the client app -- added Fluid unit (oz/mL -> fluid_unit), Date format (MM/DD vs DD/MM -> date_format, its own section since it's not an imperial/metric pair), and the Body composition silhouette picker (reused the existing web BodyCompPicker component -> body_fat_band; replaced the old 'set from mobile' note). Aligned swim to the client app: dropped the standalone Swim-distance toggle and now derive swim_unit from distance on save (mi->yd, km->m). All write to effectiveUserId (target=client in the drawer, self otherwise) and are gender/target-aware (BodyCompPicker reads the target profile's gender + body_fat_band). Affects self mode too (admin/coach own Preferences gain fluid/date/body-comp) -- intentional, consistent with the app. STILL PENDING in Phase 2: Account tab (photo editing target-aware upload; phone change + 'send code to client' via the phone-OTP fn) + Meal-layout editor (extract the slot editor from EditProfile.jsx into a shared component, reuse in target mode). NOTE: send-phone-otp is NOT in the repo functions folder (only verify-phone-otp is present alongside admin-user-management/coach-signup/delete-user/init-profile-checkpoint/send-coach-invite/stripe-webhook) -- must confirm via MCP whether send-phone-otp is deployed before wiring the admin 'send code' button. PHASE 2b (Account mirror: photo + phone) DONE 2026-06-08 (deploy index-Cp9sfJ6v.js, live verified). Verified via MCP: send-phone-otp IS deployed (v12, active, verify_jwt=true) -- its source takes a { phone } param and Twilio-Verify-scopes by NUMBER not user (auth only gates spam), so an admin can text a code to the client's new number. PHOTO: avatar storage RLS only allowed self-folder writes (auth.uid()=foldername[1], no superuser bypass), so admins couldn't set a client photo -> added migration admin_manage_any_avatar (2 additive storage.objects policies: admins (public.is_admin()) can INSERT/UPDATE any object in the avatars bucket; users keep self-only). TargetAccountTab now has a full avatar editor: pick -> reuse AvatarCropper (512² JPEG blob) -> direct storage upload to `${clientId}/avatar` (useAuth.uploadAvatar is self-bound, so direct) -> write avatar_url (cache-busted) to the client's profile; Remove sets avatar_url null. PHONE: TargetAccountTab phone field gained a Verified/Not-verified badge (from phone_verified_at, flips to Not-verified the moment the admin edits the number), a 'Send code to client' button (supabase.functions.invoke send-phone-otp with E.164 validation + sent/error states), and handleSave now nulls phone_verified_at whenever the number changes (client re-verifies on their device). Email stays read-only (Security tab's send-link). Account tab now mirrors the client minus the device-only/verification-gated bits, exactly per the decisions. REMAINING Phase 2: meal-layout editor (extract the slot editor from EditProfile.jsx into a shared component, render in target Preferences) -- last piece. Then Phase 3 (billing->feed verify), Phase 4 (sign-out-everywhere + disable-fingerprint backends), Phase 5 (mobile fingerprint-flag launch-check). PHASE 2c (meal layout) DONE 2026-06-08 (deploy index-BkflvZgD.js, live verified) -- PHASE 2 NOW COMPLETE. Extracted the meal-slot editor into a new shared component web/src/components/MealLayoutEditor.jsx (slot list + per-slot insert-divider presets/custom + reset + save; props profile/effectiveUserId/onSaved/refreshOnSave/note). Wired into AccountSettings PreferencesTab (after body stats) -- writes to effectiveUserId (client in target mode), admin-voice note. ALSO refactored EditProfile.jsx SettingsTab to use the same component (removed ~90 lines of inline meal state+handlers+JSX, kept its card wrapper+header+end-user-voice note, cleaned now-unused imports X as XIcon/Plus + the FoodLogDrawer DEFAULT_SLOTS/EXTRA_PRESETS/ANCHOR_IDS import) so there's ONE meal editor, no duplication. Build clean, both surfaces compile. ADMIN CLIENT-SETTINGS MIRROR (Account + Preferences + Security) is now a faithful editable mirror of the client app minus the device-only/verification-gated bits, exactly per the decisions. REMAINING: Phase 3 (billing->activity-feed coverage verify, NO billing page), Phase 4 (sign-out-everywhere edge fn + disable-fingerprint flag), Phase 5 (mobile fingerprint-flag launch-check). DOC-MISMATCH NOTE for CLAUDE.md: send-phone-otp IS deployed (v12) but absent from the repo supabase/functions/ folder -- repo only has verify-phone-otp; the send-phone-otp source lives only on Supabase (retrieved via MCP get_edge_function). PHASE 3 (billing -> activity feed) VERIFIED DONE 2026-06-08 -- NO CODE NEEDED, NO billing page in settings (decision 6 honored). Confirmed via MCP: the AFTER INSERT trigger billing_events_to_activity_events_trg on public.billing_events is ENABLED and runs trg_billing_event_to_activity() (SECURITY DEFINER), which fans EVERY billing_events row into activity_events as event_type='billing:'||type with full event_data (amount/currency/status/description + all stripe IDs), source='system'. The stripe-webhook edge fn writes billing_events.type using CANONICAL names (invoice_paid, invoice_failed, subscription_started, subscription_updated, subscription_cancelled, b2c_purchase, refund_issued, dispute_opened) that EXACTLY match the feed's describe() billing:* cases in AdminUserDetail -- so each transaction renders with its proper label (Invoice paid $X, Subscription started, Refund issued, Dispute opened, One-time purchase, etc.). (The lone raw 'invoice.payment_succeeded' row in billing_events was a manual test insert, not from the webhook -- ignore.) So 'every transaction reflected to the activity feed' is already true end-to-end. REMAINING: Phase 4 (sign-out-everywhere edge fn [service-role session revoke] + disable-fingerprint flag) + Phase 5 (mobile launch-check honoring the disable-fingerprint flag: clears SecureStore biometric + app lock). PHASE 4 (the 2 remote security actions) DONE 2026-06-08 (deploy index-j8Ck2seS.js, live verified; migration admin_remote_security_actions applied). Did it as a DB RPC + a flag column rather than editing the admin-user-management edge fn (simpler, fewer moving parts). MIGRATION: (1) added profiles.biometric_disabled_at timestamptz -- admin sets it; mobile clears on-device biometric+lock on next launch when this is newer than the device's enrol time (Phase 5). (2) created public.admin_revoke_user_sessions(p_user_id uuid) -- SECURITY DEFINER, is_admin()-gated, `delete from auth.sessions where user_id=p_user_id` (verified auth.sessions has user_id; refresh tokens die immediately, access tokens expire within ~1h TTL), granted execute to authenticated (the internal is_admin() check gates it; revoked from public/anon). WEB: AdminSupportActions' two former stubs are now live -- 'Disable fingerprint on all devices' does a direct profiles.update({biometric_disabled_at}) (admin RLS bypass), 'Sign out everywhere' calls the RPC; both with sending/done/error states (added a successLabel prop to SupportActionRow so they read 'Done' not 'Sent'). Couldn't happy-path test the RPC via MCP (service-role context has no auth.uid() so is_admin() is false -> raises admin_required, which is correct) -- the admin's web session will pass is_admin(); user to QA. REMAINING: Phase 5 (mobile) -- on launch, compare profiles.biometric_disabled_at to the device's stored biometric-enrol timestamp; if newer, clear SecureStore myrx.bio.* + AsyncStorage myrx.lock.enabled so fingerprint sign-in + app lock are disabled on that device. Needs storing an enrol timestamp on the device when biometric is enabled (settings.tsx) + the launch check (likely in AuthContext or _layout). PHASE 5 (mobile honors the flag) DONE 2026-06-08 (mobile tsc clean; mobile-only, no web deploy; can't QA without the device) -- T103 NOW COMPLETE. mobile/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx: (1) new SecureStore key myrx.bio.enrolledAt stamped on enableBiometric (ISO now) and deleted on disableBiometric; (2) module-level honorRemoteBiometricDisable(profile) -- if profile.biometric_disabled_at is set AND this device holds biometric creds AND disabledAt > the device's enrolledAt (missing enrol record counts as old), it wipes SecureStore myrx.bio.email/password/enrolledAt/pending + calls setLockEnabled(false) (imported from lockState); (3) called fire-and-forget from fetchProfile after setProfile, so on next launch/profile-load a device whose enrolment predates the admin's action loses fingerprint sign-in + app lock and falls back to password. Idempotent (no-creds early return). Re-enrol stamps a newer enrolledAt so the same flag won't re-clear; a fresh admin click sets a newer biometric_disabled_at to re-trigger. Only enrol site is enableBiometric (sole BIO_EMAIL_KEY writer) so all enrol paths (incl. signup BiometricScreen) are covered. ENTIRE T103 COMPLETE: admin client-settings page mirrors the client (Account photo/name/email-read-only/phone-set+send-code/dob/gender; Preferences units+fluid+date+body-fat+meal-layout; Security privacy + password/email send-links + disable-fingerprint + sign-out-everywhere), billing flows to the activity feed (no settings billing page), coaches have NO client-settings access (and the latent coach password bug is gated out). Coach does NOT mirror this (per user). QA PENDING: user to exercise the admin actions live (send-code SMS, sign-out-everywhere, disable-fingerprint end-to-end on a device).",
     "web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx (Phase 1: password gating, tab-key namespace, support-button error states); next: web/src/components/ClientSettingsDrawer.jsx, web/src/pages/admin/AdminUserDetail.jsx, new web body-fat picker + meal-layout editor, new edge fns, mobile settings.tsx launch-check; NO coach mirror per user",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T104", "Log admin account actions to the activity feed", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-07: clicked the Active toggle and nothing appeared in the Activity Feed -- 'everything should write in the activity feed, even the delete account, double check on this.' VERIFIED via DB (mcp): the timeline reads the `activity_events` table (id uuid, user_id, event_type, event_data jsonb, source, caused_by, occurred_at) -- NOT user_activity_events (a separate, mostly-unused table). Delete (account:deletion_scheduled/cancelled/deleted) and coaching (coach:assigned/detached/swapped) ALREADY log via their RPCs (schedule_account_deletion / cancel_scheduled_deletion / admin_set_athlete_coaching all insert into activity_events). The real gaps: ACTIVATE/SUSPEND (runs through the admin-user-management edge fn, never logged) and CHAT enable/disable (toggleChat does a direct profiles update, never logged).",
     "DONE 2026-06-07 (committed 3a1959a; migration log_admin_activity_rpc): new SECURITY DEFINER public.log_admin_activity(p_user_id uuid, p_event_type text, p_event_data jsonb) inserts into activity_events matching the existing pattern (source='admin', caused_by=auth.uid()); definer is required because activity_events has SELECT-only RLS (no INSERT policy). Guard = is_admin() OR is_active_coach() (is_admin() = profiles.is_superuser, so admins pass). toggleActive + toggleChat now call it best-effort (.then(ok,err) so a log failure never surfaces as an action error) with event types account:activated / account:deactivated / chat:enabled / chat:disabled; added getActivityMeta timeline labels for all four (Power / MessageCircle icons). FOLLOW-UP: settings-form edits (AccountSettings) + any other admin mutations should also log -- fold into the T103 settings rework. Coach view gets the same in the T079 coach-reflection batch. FIX 2026-06-07 (user: 'account suspension still didnt log'): the first RPC version used source='admin', but activity_events has CHECK (source IN ('trigger','rpc','client','webhook','system')) -- so EVERY admin-log insert silently failed (the client swallows the RPC error best-effort). Migration log_admin_activity_fix_source switched source to 'rpc' (it IS an RPC, matching schedule_account_deletion; admin attribution stays in event_data.admin_initiated + caused_by). Verified via a probe insert that the table accepts (account:deactivated / source=rpc passes both the source CHECK and the event_type-format CHECK ^[a-z_]+:[a-z_]+...). DB-ONLY fix -- no web redeploy; the already-deployed client now logs on the next toggle. Event_type format CHECK is why types must be lowercase domain:action (account:deactivated, chat:enabled -- all valid).",
     "supabase migrations log_admin_activity_rpc + log_admin_activity_fix_source; web/src/pages/admin/AdminUserDetail.jsx (toggleActive/toggleChat log calls + getActivityMeta cases)",
     "2026-06-07"),

    ("T105", "Messages page: deep-link doesn't open transcript on mobile; conversation scrolls top-to-bottom on open", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-07: (1) 'when i clicked on the message button on mobile web, it took me to the messages page, but it didnt open the message page of the client'; (2) 'even on desktop web, when i click on a client's msg page, it opens the page, but scrolls from top to bottom instead of opening directly to the latest msg.' Two distinct bugs in AdminMessages.jsx MessagesTab. (1) MOBILE DEEP-LINK: the split layout uses a `showList` state -- on a narrow screen the client list shows when showList=true (`${showList ? 'flex' : 'hidden'} md:flex`) and the transcript panel shows when showList=false (`${!showList ? 'flex' : 'hidden'} md:flex`). List-row clicks go through selectConversation(uid) which sets selectedId AND showList=false. But the `?userId=` deep-link handler (fired by the 'Message athlete' pill on AdminUserDetail) called setSelectedId(target) directly, bypassing selectConversation -- so showList stayed true and mobile kept showing the list. (2) SCROLL: the scroll-to-bottom effect used `behavior: 'smooth'` on EVERY run, including conversation-open, so opening a chat animated the whole transcript top->bottom (reads as a 'where am I' scroll). Desktop shows both panes so the mobile bug wasn't visible there, but the smooth-on-open scroll was.",
     "DONE 2026-06-07 (deploy index-JF861ybb.js -> index-CeCe7Exe.js after the coach twin fix; live hash verified == local on myrxfit.com both times). Fixed on BOTH the admin (AdminMessages.jsx) AND coach (CoachMessages.jsx) surfaces in the same turn -- per the cross-platform bug rule (a reported bug gets fixed on every surface where it exists), and because CoachMessages is an ALREADY-SHIPPED standalone page (NOT part of the deferred T079 client-detail reflection batch). It mirrors AdminMessages line-for-line and had both identical bugs live (coach deep-link key is ?clientId= from the CoachClientDetail 'Message athlete' pill; admin is ?userId= from AdminUserDetail). (1) deep-link handler now also calls setShowList(false) when a match is found, so mobile reveals the transcript panel (desktop unaffected -- both panes always render at md+). (2) scroll effect tracks the previous selectedId via a new prevSelectedRef; conversation OPEN/SWITCH (selectedId changed) -> `behavior:'auto'` (instant jump to newest), new message while same conversation open (messages changed, selectedId same) -> `behavior:'smooth'` (incoming bubble glides in). Typing still never scrolls (unchanged). Both fixes are pure client UI -- no DB/RPC. WORKTREE TRAP NOTE: Glob('web/src/pages/coach/CoachMessages.jsx') returned 'No files found' because Glob defaults to the stale worktree CWD (.claude/worktrees/tender-tharp-e1109d) which lacks the coach pages; the file exists in MAIN. Always edit/build via absolute C:/Users/motaz/OneDrive/Desktop/MyRX/... paths (per the T080 multi-worktree lesson).",
     "web/src/pages/admin/AdminMessages.jsx + web/src/pages/coach/CoachMessages.jsx (both: deep-link setShowList(false); prevSelectedRef instant-vs-smooth scroll)",
     "2026-06-07"),

    ("T106", "Activity feed icon colors must match each domain's canonical app-wide color", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-07: 'the activity feed uses different colors for some icons ... some icons that are green on other pages are another color in the feed, the weight which should be green is purple, the cardio which is supposed to be amber is something else, check other pages colors.' The Activity Feed's describe() (AdminUserDetail.jsx) hand-picked per-event colors that disagreed with the domain palette every OTHER surface uses. Audited the canonical colors: bodyweight=emerald (DashboardBodyweightBlock Scale + AdminUserBody), calories=amber (DashboardCaloriesBlock Apple), heart=red (DashboardHeartBlock), sleep=indigo (DashboardSleepBlock), hydration=cyan (DashboardHydrationBlock), strength=blue + cardio=amber (AdminUserActivity filter pills L195-196: strength text-blue-400 / cardio text-amber-400 + Activity icon; locked in CLAUDE.md 'strength keeps blue, cardio keeps amber'). Feed offenders: training:bodyweight_insert was purple-400 (should be emerald), training:efforts_insert was always blue-400 regardless of type (a CARDIO effort should be amber, not blue), training:wearable_workouts_insert was emerald-400 (emerald is bodyweight's color now; a wearable workout is a cardio session -> amber). Also found a sibling: DashboardEffortsBlock's per-row cardio dot used bg-orange-400 (non-canonical) instead of amber.",
     "DONE 2026-06-07 (deploy index-BDgD5a74.js, live hash verified == local). AdminUserDetail.jsx describe(): (1) training:efforts_insert now SPLITS on d.type -- cardio -> Activity icon + text-amber-400, strength -> Dumbbell + text-blue-400 (exactly the AdminUserActivity Strength|Cardio pill colors+icons); (2) training:bodyweight_insert purple-400 -> emerald-400; (3) training:wearable_workouts_insert emerald-400 -> amber-400 (cardio domain; Activity icon already matched). DashboardEffortsBlock.jsx: cardio row-dot bg-orange-400 -> bg-amber-400. Left UNTOUCHED (correctly): the account/billing/chat lifecycle rows keep their SEMANTIC palette (emerald=positive, red=failure/destructive, amber=warning, zinc/muted=neutral) -- those events have no per-domain color elsewhere and the user didn't flag them; and the non-domain orange/purple schemes in AdminMovements (equipment-type badges: Carry=orange, Assisted=purple) + AdminDashboard ('no-nutrition' flag=orange) which are their own internally-consistent category schemes, not activity-domain colors. SCOPE: the Activity Feed currently lives ONLY in AdminUserDetail (CoachClientDetail has no Activity tab yet -- 4-tab Dashboard/Efforts/Bodyweight/Calories), so no coach twin to mirror today; the DashboardEffortsBlock fix is a shared component so it's automatically correct wherever it renders (incl. future coach use). NOTE: clarified mid-task via AskUserQuestion (uniform vs semantic) -- user rejected both framings and specified the real ask = match other-page domain colors; built to that. CALORIES CORRECTION 2026-06-07 (deploy index-CH6gMukt.js, live hash verified): the T106 first pass wrongly assumed calories=amber (it had copied DashboardCaloriesBlock's amber, which was ITSELF wrong). User: 'food logging is red not amber, check the red in cals page.' Verified the canonical calories/food domain color = RED: the cals page hero 'Daily calorie target' uses Flame + text-red-400 + the big red number + red BMR/TDEE active pills (CalorieDashboard.jsx L318/321/330), the web nav Calories item uses the Flame icon (Navbar.jsx L18), and AdminUserDetail's OWN food snapshot badge already used Flame+red (L1167). So amber was never the calories color -- it's only the 'near-target' rung of the green/amber/red traffic-light STATUS system (statusFor in CalorieTrendGraph), which is semantic and stays. Fixed: feed training:food_logs_insert + training:calorie_plans_insert amber-400 -> red-400; DashboardCaloriesBlock iconTint amber-400 -> red-400 AND its 'Daily target' headline stat amber-400 -> red-400 (matches the cals page red daily-target). ICON: user explicitly said 'i actually like the apple for cals' -> KEPT the Apple icon everywhere (did NOT switch to Flame despite the nav/hero using Flame). Heart is also red (Heart icon) -- calories (Apple) + heart (Heart) both red, differentiated by icon, which is the app's actual convention. The CalorieTrendGraph traffic-light bands (on=emerald/near=amber/off=red) were left untouched -- they're status, not domain color.",
     "web/src/pages/admin/AdminUserDetail.jsx (describe() training rows); web/src/components/DashboardEffortsBlock.jsx (cardio dot)",
     "2026-06-07"),

    ("T107", "Calorie/food domain icon = Apple across all cal pages (web + mobile), icon-only", "Coach/Admin", "Web+Mobile", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-07: 'lets reflect it on all cal pages on web and mobile.' MISFIRE: I read 'it' as the calories=red COLOR and started a broad amber->red audit/migration across all calorie surfaces. User interrupted: 'what are you doing, i didnt ask to change any colors, i just said change the icon for cals to be the apple, keep all colors as they were.' Then clarified the end state via the follow-up question: 'food logging and cals are apple and red.' So the ACTUAL ask was ICON-ONLY: make the calorie/food domain icon the APPLE everywhere it was a Flame, and keep EVERY color exactly as-is (the main cals icons are already red from T106's b4fa286, so they become red apples; the macro Fat amber, the near-target traffic-light amber, the pending Clock amber, and the energy-balance hues all stay). NO color edits at all this round.",
     "DONE 2026-06-07 (web deploy index-BY06pom1.js, live hash verified == local; mobile tsc --noEmit clean). Audited every calorie/food surface on both platforms via 2 parallel read-only agents first (classified each amber as DOMAIN-ACCENT vs MACRO-COLOR(Fat) vs STATUS-TRAFFIC-LIGHT(near-target) vs ENERGY-BALANCE vs OTHER) so I'd touch ONLY the domain icon and nothing else. Flame->Apple swaps, colors preserved verbatim: WEB -- CalorieDashboard.jsx hero (was Flame+red->Apple+red) + empty-state 'No intake plan yet' (Flame+amber->Apple+amber, color kept), Navbar.jsx Calories nav item (Flame->Apple). MOBILE -- calories.tsx hero (Flame+red->Apple+red), 2 empty states 'Set up your plan' + 'Set a new plan' (Flame+amber->Apple+amber, color kept), dashboard.tsx calorie feed row (Flame+red->Apple+red) + food-streak chip both states (Flame red/muted->Apple, colors kept). Each file's lucide import Flame->Apple (Flame fully unused after). LEFT UNTOUCHED per 'keep all colors': macro Fat=amber (calories.tsx/CalorieDashboard/FoodLogDrawer/MacroPlanEditor/PlanWizardSheet), near-target traffic-light amber (CalorieStrip status dot + CalorieTrendGraph band), the mobile PendingView Clock 'your plan is on its way' (it's a waiting STATUS, stays a Clock+amber, NOT the calorie icon), energy-balance emerald/blue, and the food-logging RED from T106/b4fa286 (user confirmed 'apple and red' -> kept). The DashboardCaloriesBlock + activity-feed food rows were ALREADY apple+red from b4fa286, no change. PROCESS SCARS (self-inflicted, fixed in-turn): twice botched a replace_all by dropping the trailing space in new_string ('<Flame className=\"h-4 w-4 ' -> '<Apple className=\"h-4 w-4' gave 'w-4text-...'; '<Flame ' -> '<Apple' gave '<Applesize='); caught both via grep and repaired. Also hit 'File has not been read yet' on Navbar.jsx (only grepped, never Read) -- had to Read before Edit. NOTE: the empty-state apples are still AMBER (kept per 'keep all colors'); if the user wants those red too it's a 1-line follow-up. Web end-user Navbar.jsx was included for completeness (App.jsx still wires it) though web end-user surfaces are largely deprecated. FOLLOW-UP SWEEP 2026-06-08 (user: 'the radialnav still has flame' -> then I did the comprehensive grep I should have done first; web deploy index-DPvTfNbU.js verified, mobile tsc clean): my first pass only covered the calorie PAGES (the 2 audit agents scoped to pages, not nav/feed/overview/landing components), so I MISSED several calorie-domain Flames. Fixed them all in one sweep, Flame->Apple, colors kept: mobile/src/components/RadialNav.tsx (the radial nav menu Calories entry — what the user caught), web AdminFeed.jsx (calorie feed-row icon, red), web AdminOverview.jsx (calorie feed icon + 'Nutrition Active' stat, red), web AdminUserDetail.jsx (food snapshot badges L1168/1173, red/muted), web CoachClientDetail.jsx (food snapshot badges L560/565, red/muted), web Landing.jsx ('Calorie lab' feature card). Removed the now-unused Flame import from each (Apple already imported in AdminUserDetail/CoachClientDetail; replaced Flame->Apple in the import for AdminFeed/AdminOverview/Landing/RadialNav). The ONLY Flame left app-wide is AdminDashboard.jsx 'On a Streak' (3+ consecutive weeks) -- that's the training-STREAK fire metaphor, NOT calories, correctly kept. LESSON (logged so the next color/icon-domain task starts right): when a request is 'reflect X across the whole app', grep the ENTIRE codebase for the token FIRST (grep -rn 'Flame' web/src mobile) and classify every hit, instead of scoping to the obvious 'pages' -- nav menus / feed config maps / overview stat tiles / landing cards / snapshot badges all carry domain icons too. PROCESS SCAR (repeat of T107's earlier one): botched the badge replace_all THREE times by dropping the trailing space in new_string ('shrink-0 ' -> 'shrink-0' gave 'shrink-0text-'); always keep old_string and new_string boundary-aligned on whitespace, or include the char after the space.",
     "web/src/components/CalorieDashboard.jsx; web/src/components/Navbar.jsx; mobile/app/(app)/calories.tsx; mobile/app/(app)/dashboard.tsx",
     "2026-06-07"),

    ("T108", "Fix the admin email-change link + audit all client-settings support-action links", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08: 'fix the email change link and double check on all other links like the password change or the phone change or whatever.' The 'Send email-change link' support action (AccountSettings AdminSupportActions) was BROKEN: it called supabase.auth.resetPasswordForEmail(profile.email, { redirectTo: '/auth?mode=update-email' }) -- a PASSWORD-RESET (type=recovery) email pointed at a /auth?mode=update-email page that DOESN'T EXIST (mode=update-email appears nowhere in the app). Clicking it ran the recovery flow -> AuthConfirm's 'Set a new password' form (wrong) or dumped the client on the generic /auth page. Worse, a one-click 'send link' can't ever change an email -- nobody supplies the NEW address, and GoTrue has NO admin-triggered 'client confirms via link' email-change path (the only confirm flow is the user-initiated updateUser({email}) the client runs in their OWN app). And the client is mobile-only.",
     "DONE 2026-06-08 (edge fn admin-user-management v7 deployed; web deploy index-PsRrk6KY.js, live verified). AUDIT of all support-action links/flows: (1) PASSWORD RESET -- VERIFIED WORKING, no change: resetPasswordForEmail sends a type=recovery email whose link Supabase renders as {SiteURL}/auth/confirm?token_hash=...&type=recovery; AuthConfirm.jsx verifyOtp(type=recovery) -> 'Set a new password' form -> updateUser({password}). Same flow the end-user forgot-password uses. redirectTo only affects post-reset navigation (irrelevant for a mobile client), so the admin's no-redirectTo call still lands on the recovery form. (2) EMAIL CHANGE -- FIXED: replaced the broken one-click link with an inline 'Change account email' field (admin types the new address) wired to a NEW 'change_email' action on the admin-user-management edge fn (superuser-gated, cannot_modify_self/admin guards reused) that calls auth.admin.updateUserById(target, { email, email_confirm: true }) -> applies immediately, surfaces 'already in use' errors. Chose admin-direct (not client-confirm) because GoTrue offers no admin-triggered confirm-link flow + the client is mobile-only; documented this in code + flagged to the user with the option to do a heavier client-confirm flow if wanted. NOTE: email_confirm:true means NO notification email to the client (no mailer in edge fns); acceptable for an admin tool, flagged. profiles has no email column (email lives in auth.users, surfaced via get_users_for_admin) so the read-only Account-tab email display is stale until next load -- minor, consistent with other admin edits. (3) PHONE -- VERIFIED WORKING (T103 Phase 2b): admin sets profiles.phone (+ nulls phone_verified_at on change) and 'Send code to client' invokes the deployed send-phone-otp edge fn (takes a {phone} param, Twilio-Verify-scoped by number) -> SMS to the client -> client enters it in their mobile app (verify-phone-otp). Not a 'link' -- in-app OTP. (4) DISABLE FINGERPRINT / SIGN OUT EVERYWHERE -- the Phase 4/5 actions, already verified. Updated the Account-tab email note + the AdminSupportActions doc comment to match the new 'Change account email' field.",
     "web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx (AdminSupportActions: inline change-email form replacing the broken link; note + comment updates); supabase edge fn admin-user-management (added change_email action, v7)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T109", "Settings mirror drift — distance/fluid/date unit cards didn't match the client app", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (frustrated, recurring mirror-accuracy complaint): 'why does distance show different between mobile and web, why do i have to always find that you dont mirror correctly everything we do?' Compared the web admin Preferences mirror (AccountSettings PreferencesTab) line-by-line against the live mobile client settings (mobile/app/(app)/settings.tsx, the PreferencesTab unit cards L1533-1581 + body-comp L1662-1672). DRIFT FOUND: (1) DISTANCE card -- mobile shows 'mi · yd' / 'Miles & yards' and 'km · m' / 'Km & metres' (ONE imperial-vs-metric choice that drives BOTH running/cycling distance AND swim unit); my Phase-2a web mirror showed plain 'mi'/'Miles' + 'km'/'Kilometres', hiding that it also sets swim. This is the one the user spotted. (2) FLUID sub -- mobile 'Fluid ounces', web had 'Ounces'. (3) DATE FORMAT -- mobile renders it as a 4th/5th card INSIDE the same Imperial|Metric units grid with labels 'MM/DD'/'DD/MM' + subs 'Imperial'/'Metric'; web had it in a SEPARATE section with 'MM / DD'/'DD / MM' + subs 'Month first'/'Day first'. (4) BODY-COMP footnote -- mobile passes showFootnote={false} inside Body stats; web added a 'The Calories plan uses this...' footnote.",
     "DONE 2026-06-08 (deploy index-tkWDJN8Q.js, live verified). Aligned the web Preferences unit cards to the mobile client EXACTLY: Distance -> 'mi · yd'/'Miles & yards' + 'km · m'/'Km & metres'; Fluid sub -> 'Fluid ounces'; Date format -> moved INTO the Imperial|Metric units grid as a UnitRow with 'MM/DD'/'Imperial' + 'DD/MM'/'Metric' (removed the separate section); Body composition -> dropped the footnote to match showFootnote=false. Underlying behavior was already correct (swim_unit derives from distance on save since Phase 2a) -- this was a LABEL/PRESENTATION drift only. Weight + Height cards already matched (Pounds/Kilograms, Feet & inches/Centimetres). PROCESS NOTE (the user's real complaint): when mirroring a surface, diff the actual client source card-by-card (labels + subs + layout + which section each control sits in), not just the data/behavior -- presentation drift is what the user sees and keeps catching. Should have done this card-by-card diff during Phase 2a instead of writing approximate labels.",
     "web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx (PreferencesTab: Distance/Fluid/Date-format unit cards + body-comp footnote, matched to mobile settings.tsx)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T110", "Admin client-settings mirror showed DEFAULTS not the client's real prefs (RPC omitted columns) + body-comp picker drift", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (still frustrated, sent 6 screenshots): 'the choices between the client on mobile and web are different ... im talking about the client's settings ... look at the screenshot.' The screenshots (admin's 'Motaz Jarrah's Settings' drawer vs motaz's mobile) showed: web Body composition = Average selected w/ ranges Lean ≤12% / Average 12-22% / High >22% and NO descriptions; mobile = Lean selected w/ ≤14% BF / 15-24% BF / ≥25% BF + descriptions ('Visible muscle definition...', etc.) + 'Pick the silhouette...' subtitle. Also web fluid=oz vs mobile mL, web meal=4 slots (Breakfast/Lunch/Dinner/Snacks) vs mobile 5 (incl. a custom Post-Workout). ROOT CAUSE (the big one): AdminUserDetail loads the client via the get_user_for_admin RPC, whose RETURNS TABLE column list was missing the NEWER columns -- fluid_unit, date_format, body_fat_band, meal_slots_default, share_online_status, share_last_seen, phone_verified_at. So the mirror received undefined for those and fell back to component DEFAULTS (oz / 'average' / DEFAULT_SLOTS / true), regardless of the client's stored values. Verified motaz's DB row: distance=km, fluid=mL, body_fat=lean, meal_slots_default=5 incl post_workout. SECOND issue: the web BodyCompPicker component itself was a stale port -- wrong BF% bands (≤12/12-22/>22 vs mobile ≤14/15-24/≥25), no 'BF' suffix, no per-card descriptions, no 'Pick the silhouette' subtitle.",
     "DONE 2026-06-08 (migration get_user_for_admin_add_pref_columns; web deploy index-BYJTiD_c.js, live verified). (1) DROP+CREATE get_user_for_admin adding the 7 missing columns (fluid_unit, date_format, body_fat_band, meal_slots_default, share_online_status, share_last_seen, phone_verified_at) to both the RETURNS TABLE and the SELECT (return-type change requires drop-then-create per the Supabase RPC rule). This single fix corrects the SELECTED values across the mirror -- fluid now reads mL, body-fat reads lean, meal shows all 5 slots incl Post-Workout, the phone Verified/Not-verified badge reads phone_verified_at, and the Security privacy toggles now reflect the client's ACTUAL share_online_status/share_last_seen instead of defaulting to true (a latent bug -- the toggles were showing ON for everyone). (2) Rewrote web/src/components/BodyCompPicker.jsx to mirror mobile/src/components/BodyCompPicker.tsx EXACTLY: male ≤14% BF / 15-24% BF / ≥25% BF + female ≤20% / 21-30% / ≥31% BF, per-card descriptions, the 'Pick the silhouette that most closely matches your current body.' subtitle, and a showFootnote prop (default true; AccountSettings passes false to match mobile settings showFootnote=false; the macro editor uses compact which suppresses subtitle/desc/footnote so its dense layout is unchanged). LESSON (the recurring complaint's real root): a 'mirror' built on an admin RPC is only as complete as that RPC's column list -- when mobile adds a profile column, the get_user_for_admin RPC must be extended too, or the web mirror silently shows defaults. Audited: all columns the settings mirror reads are now returned. PRIOR near-misses (T109 labels) were real but secondary; THIS (RPC columns) was why the selected values were wrong.",
     "supabase migration get_user_for_admin_add_pref_columns (DROP+CREATE with 7 added columns); web/src/components/BodyCompPicker.jsx (full rewrite to mobile parity); web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx (showFootnote=false)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T111", "Real-time reflection of settings changes across all settings pages (web + mobile)", "Coach/Admin", "Web+Mobile", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08: 'i need changes to be reflected in real time, the moment i click save it reflects on their account and they can actually see the toggles happen, on all settings pages' + clarification 'not just mirroring, any update we do.' For settings: when the admin saves a client's setting, the CLIENT (and any other viewer) should see the toggles flip LIVE, across all settings sections + all settings surfaces (mobile client settings + web admin mirror + web own-profile pages). FINDING (verified): the realtime DATA path already exists on mobile -- mobile/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx subscribes to the user's OWN profiles row (postgres_changes UPDATE, filter id=eq.user.id, ~L400-457) and calls fetchProfile on UPDATE, so the in-context `profile` updates within ~1-2s of the admin's save. THE GAP: every settings screen (mobile settings.tsx tabs + web AccountSettings tabs) seeds its toggle values into LOCAL useState ONCE on mount, so it never repaints from the live profile -> nothing visibly happens.",
     "DONE (Jun 8 2026), bidirectional, all 4 directions. DATA path was already live on BOTH ends -- no new subscriptions needed: (a) mobile AuthContext subscribes to the user's OWN profiles row (postgres_changes UPDATE, filter id=eq.user.id) -> fetchProfile, PLUS catch-up fetches on channel-SUBSCRIBED + AppState=active; (b) web AuthContext has the equivalent self-profile sub (channel profile-self-${id}); (c) AdminUserDetail ALREADY had a profiles UPDATE(id=eq.clientId) sub that merges payload.new into profile via setProfile(prev => ({...prev, ...next})) -- the merge (not RPC re-call) is deliberate because the realtime row carries no email (email lives on auth.users, hydrated by the RPC into prev). THE ONLY GAP was the UI: each tab seeded local useState ONCE on mount and never repainted. FIX = diff-based useEffect([profile]) in each tab that re-derives ONLY the fields whose value changed vs a useRef snapshot (so an external change flips the toggle while in-progress local edits to OTHER fields survive; first run just snapshots). Added to: web AccountSettings PreferencesTab (units/fluid/date/body-comp/weight/height), SecurityTab (share_online/share_last_seen), TargetAccountTab (name/gender/dob/phone/avatar/weight/height); web MealLayoutEditor (slot-id-sequence diff); mobile settings.tsx AccountTab (name/gender/dob/avatar-when-not-mid-crop), PreferencesTab (units/fluid/date/body-comp/weight/height), SecurityTab (share toggles). Also HARDENED the pre-existing mobile meal-slots effect (was an unconditional re-seed -> would clobber unsaved slot edits whenever realtime fired for any unrelated field; now slot-id-sequence diff). Excluded device-local prefs (enter-to-send, biometric, app-lock -- not in profile). VERIFIED: web build clean + deployed (index-0eZLHkR3.js live hash == local), mobile tsc --noEmit clean + dev bundle reloaded over wireless adb (ReactNativeJS Running main, no fatal errors). CLAUDE.md auto-synced: removed bogus profiles.email column (it's on auth.users) + documented the T111 realtime contract + the missing pref/privacy columns. Web self ProfileTab (name/avatar text fields) + mobile AccountTab phone (country-split + verify flow) intentionally left non-live -- low value, high risk; can revisit if asked. USER ACCEPTANCE (visual toggle-flip on the phone) is the user's to confirm per the no-screenshot mobile-verify rule.",
     "mobile/app/(app)/settings.tsx; web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx; web/src/components/MealLayoutEditor.jsx; web/src/pages/admin/AdminUserDetail.jsx (sub pre-existing); web/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx (sub pre-existing); mobile/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx (sub pre-existing)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T112", "Add a VERIFY-EVERY-UPDATE rule to CLAUDE.md + confirm pipeline currency", "Process", "Docs", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08: 'are you updating the task pipeline? read claude.md to refresh your memory ... add to claude.md something that makes you test the things you mirror in a way to catch these issues ... not just mirroring, any update we do, make it so you can test it so we dont face these issues ever again.' The recurring pain (T109/T110): mirrors/updates shipped looking fine on DEFAULT data but were wrong on real data -- admin RPC omitted columns so the mirror showed defaults; label drift; default-masking -- and a green build + matching deploy hash was being treated as 'done' without verifying functional correctness against real data. The user kept being the one to catch it.",
     "DONE 2026-06-08. Added a new MANDATORY rule to the MAIN-repo CLAUDE.md Working Relationship block: 'VERIFY EVERY UPDATE AGAINST REAL DATA -- it shipped != it works' (right after the WEB-SEARCH-FIRST rule), with a 4-point checklist applied to every data-driven change: (1) trace the read path end-to-end -- the source query/RPC must actually return every field the UI reads, and any SECURITY DEFINER RPC with a hand-written column list (get_user_for_admin & friends) must be extended whenever mobile adds a profiles column; (2) test with REAL non-default data via the Supabase MCP (defaults mask bugs) and, when the UI isn't reachable, cross-check stored DB values field-by-field against the read path; (3) for mirrors, diff the LIVE source control-by-control (label/sub/option-values/section/data), never from memory; (4) observe the result via the tools, don't assume -- 'deployed, please verify' isn't verification, and when a check is impossible from here say so + name the exact thing for the user to check. Confirmed the pipeline is current: T103-T110 are all logged + committed; added T111 (the realtime settings feature, Pending) per CAPTURE-FIRST. NOTE: edited the MAIN-repo CLAUDE.md (authoritative, what the user reads/commits); the worktree copy at .claude/worktrees/... is the known-stale divergent one and is NOT the source of truth.",
     "CLAUDE.md (Working Relationship MANDATORY block: new VERIFY-EVERY-UPDATE rule); scripts/build_task_pipeline_xlsx.py (T111 + T112)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T113", "Client settings drawer: Delete account only on the Account tab + always reopen on Account", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (with screenshot of the admin client-settings drawer for Motaz): 'the delete account button should be part of the account page and only on the account page, and when i close the drawer and open it again it should be on the account page again not on the last page that was accessed.' Two bugs: (1) the DANGER ZONE / Delete-account node was rendered by ClientSettingsDrawer OUTSIDE AccountSettings, at the bottom of the drawer body -> it showed on EVERY tab (Account/Preferences/Security), not just Account. (2) AccountSettings stored the target-mode active tab in usePersistedState('myrx:settings_tab:client', clearOnUnmount) -> on reopen it restored the last-accessed tab from localStorage instead of landing on Account.",
     "FIX (web only; the drawer is admin-web): (1) AccountSettings now takes a `dangerZone` prop and renders it as its OWN card BELOW the tab card, gated on `activeTab === 'account'` -> Delete shows on the Account tab only. ClientSettingsDrawer forwards `dangerZone={dangerZone}` into AccountSettings and no longer renders its own bottom-of-drawer Danger-zone block. Self-mode callers (AdminProfile/CoachProfile) don't pass dangerZone, so it never renders there (CoachProfile keeps its separate self-delete section). (2) Target-mode tab state switched from usePersistedState to a plain useState('account'): the drawer unmounts on close (`if (!open) return null`), so plain state resets to Account on every reopen. usePersistedState is still called unconditionally (rules of hooks) but, in target mode, points at a throwaway key ('myrx:settings_tab:__drawer_unused') so it can neither restore the last client tab nor clobber the admin's self-mode tab memory; self mode keeps its persisted-tab behaviour. VERIFIED: build clean + deployed (live index-Bd0kDH8v.js == local); curled the deployed AccountSettings chunk and confirmed it contains 'Danger zone' + '__drawer_unused' and NO longer contains the old 'myrx:settings_tab:client' key.",
     "web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx; web/src/components/ClientSettingsDrawer.jsx",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T114", "Enter-to-send: keep per-device (not in admin mirror) + remove dead web enter-to-send code", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08: 'why wasnt chat enter to send switch added to settings' (re the admin client-settings mirror). EXPLANATION: enter-to-send IS present where it can be -- the client's own mobile Preferences and the admin/coach's OWN web Preferences -- but it's a PER-DEVICE preference (web localStorage 'myrx_enter_to_send' / mobile AsyncStorage), NOT a profiles column. So it's deliberately hidden in the admin client-settings mirror (AccountSettings showPerDevice = viewerRole==='self'): there's no account-level value to read, and a toggle there would flip the ADMIN's own browser, not the client's. Offered to promote it to a synced profiles.enter_to_send column so it'd show in the mirror + sync across devices.",
     "User chose: KEEP it per-device ('if this is the right way for it to be keep it this way, i dont really need it that much'), and remove the dead web enter-to-send code. DONE: removed the dead enter-to-send toggle from EditProfile.jsx's SettingsTab -- the whole default EditProfile component + SettingsTab are dead (App.jsx routes nothing to them; only the named ProfileTab export is imported by AccountSettings, per the App.jsx:26 comment + route audit). Deleted: the CornerDownLeft import, the module-level ENTER_KEY const, the enterToSend useState, and the entire 'Messaging' card JSX. Verified no enterToSend/ENTER_KEY/CornerDownLeft refs remain in EditProfile.jsx. LIVE enter-to-send code KEPT (verified as real consumers): AccountSettings self-mode toggle (the setter), AdminMessages reply box (reads ENTER_KEY at L189 -> keydown L390), CoachMessages, SuggestionDrawer. Build: byte-identical bundle (index-Bd0kDH8v.js + AccountSettings-B6liLL8o.js unchanged) -- the dead EditProfile default/SettingsTab were already tree-shaken, so this is a source-only cleanup; redeployed to keep deployed==source. NOTE for a future pass: the ENTIRE SettingsTab + default EditProfile() are dead (only ProfileTab is used) -- a fuller cleanup could delete both, left out of scope here.",
     "web/src/pages/EditProfile.jsx",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T115", "Web dead-code sweep — delete unused files / exports / deps (knip-driven)", "Web", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (after the EditProfile enter-to-send removal): 'if anything is not used delete it and clean up.' Mandate to remove ALL dead code in the web app, not just the one toggle. Ran knip for an authoritative list, then verified each item by hand (knip is blind to Cloudflare Pages Functions, the service worker, and wouter routes, so it false-positives those).",
     "DONE + deployed (live index-CRGxmhus.js == local), build green throughout. REMOVED — dead files: src/App.css (unimported default), src/lib/planPresets.js (BodyCompPicker carries its own bands since the T110 rewrite), src/lib/profile.js (the web athlete ProtectedLayout that gated on isProfileComplete is gone; mobile src/lib/profile.ts is the live copy), src/components/FoodLogDrawer.jsx (~500-line dead end-user drawer; its only live content — DEFAULT_SLOTS/ANCHOR_IDS/EXTRA_PRESETS, imported by MealLayoutEditor — moved to new src/lib/mealSlots.js, import updated). EditProfile.jsx: deleted the unrouted SettingsTab + default EditProfile() + their private helpers (UnitCard/TabBtn/heightToDisplay) + now-orphaned imports (useLocation, useTheme, ArrowLeft, Sun, Moon, MealLayoutEditor); kept only the live ProfileTab named export. Lib exports: delegated to the refactor-cleaner agent with a strict per-symbol protocol (grep src/ AND functions/ for each; delete-whole if entirely unused, un-export only if used internally, skip if used) — result 18 deleted whole + 8 un-exported + 0 skipped across authErrors/calorieFormulas/chartTooltipScope/cookieConsent/countries/foodFilters/foodLibrary/formulas/imageUtils/movements/serverError; then chased the cascades myself (formulas.js orphaned consts DUMBBELL_KEYWORDS/BAR_WEIGHT/PLATE_SIZES/MIN_INCREMENT; movements.js BODYWEIGHT_EXERCISE_NAMES + ASSISTED_MACHINE_NAMES, orphaned once getEquipmentType was removed — BODYWEIGHT_LIST stayed, still used by STRENGTH_MOVEMENTS). Deps: removed unused clsx + tslib + sharp; added the previously-unlisted libphonenumber-js@^1.12.41 (ProfileTab uses AsYouType); npm install pruned 27 packages. KEPT despite knip flagging them (verified NOT dead): functions/api/off-search.js (AdminFoodLibrary calls /api/off-search at runtime) + public/sw.js (service worker, registered at runtime); src/hooks/useIsPhone.js — I deleted it then RESTORED it via git after catching that CLAUDE.md locks it (May 27 2026) as the REQUIRED route-gate hook (unused today but mandated going forward — a knip false-negative-on-intent that the 'delete unused' rule must not blindly remove); src/lib/foodLibrary.js — went unused after FoodLogDrawer deletion; initially kept on a Phase-D hunch, then DELETED Jun 2026 after the user asked about it and I verified the admin Food Library barcode scanner uses a SEPARATE path (BarcodeScanner.jsx + /api/off-search Pages Function + foodFilters.js), NOT foodLibrary — so removing it can't affect the scanner. Restorable from git if a future food feature needs the USDA/D1 worker search. Also fixed a stale CLAUDE.md note that wrongly claimed the AdminFoodLibrary scanner had been removed. CLAUDE.md auto-synced: new 'Web dead-code cleanup batch (Jun 2026)' note + fixed the FoodLogDrawer/profile.js stale references. LESSON: knip 'unused' != safe-to-delete — Pages Functions, the SW, and CLAUDE.md-mandated-but-not-yet-adopted utilities all look unused but aren't; always reconcile against runtime invocation + documented intent before deleting.",
     "web/src/pages/EditProfile.jsx; web/src/lib/mealSlots.js (new); web/src/components/MealLayoutEditor.jsx; web/src/lib/{authErrors,calorieFormulas,chartTooltipScope,cookieConsent,countries,foodFilters,formulas,imageUtils,movements,serverError}.js; web/package.json; deleted: web/src/App.css + web/src/lib/planPresets.js + web/src/lib/profile.js + web/src/components/FoodLogDrawer.jsx + web/src/lib/foodLibrary.js; CLAUDE.md",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T116", "Admin portal: rework Client Overview into a holistic platform command center", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 reworked the admin Client Overview (AdminDashboard.jsx) ground-up (like the profile-card rework). One-question-at-a-time design flow, FINAL decisions: (1) the admin wears two hats -- platform admin (all users + all coaches) AND coach of a few. (2) ONE holistic platform-command-center page (NOT three separate views), with segment filter pills (All / My clients / Coaches / Athletes) + status pills. (3) List = alphabetical A->Z always, NO sort dropdown; attention shown via per-row LEDs + pills, not sort order. (4) LED keys off WEIGH-IN + WORKOUT logging (NOT food, NOT training-PRs), 5-day line. (5) LED colors: green = both within 5d, amber = one axis >5d, red = both >5d, grey = new/nothing logged. (6) Athlete pills = 'No weigh-in . Nd' / 'No workout . Nd' / 'No macro plan' / 'Macro goal reached' / 'New' (retire old food/streak/PR pills). (7) Keep food line as X/14 (food_logs, last 14 days) + last-active line; the WEIGH-IN STREAK is DEFERRED to v2 (T117). (8) Tiles = ALL of them (not capped at 6), each show/hide-able via a Customize panel (default all-on, persisted) with info-on-hover on every tile AND the same info beside each Customize toggle. Tile set: Members (all/coaches/athletes/my) [live], Total MRR [billing], Coach revenue starter/pro/elite [billing], Athlete revenue corerx/fullrx [billing+IAP], Trials [billing], At-risk/retention [billing], Coach capacity/upsell [live], Engagement [live]. Dormant tiles show a 'live at launch' placeholder, never a fake $0. (9) Coach rows = adaptive variant: LED = subscription health (active/trial/lapsed), pills = tier + trial/active/lapsed + capacity (n/cap), mini roster-health line. (10) Scope = full roster (all clients the admin oversees) + a 'My clients' filter (admin coaches only 1 today, so a strict My-Clients page would be near-empty).",
     "BUILDING v1 this run. DATA (verified): get_users_for_admin (email + base) MERGED with a direct profiles select (coach_id / is_coach / is_superuser / b2c_subscription_tier -- admin has the superusers_read_all_profiles RLS SELECT policy, so no RPC change needed) + bodyweight (latest weigh-in) + efforts (latest workout, 90d window) + food_logs (14d distinct days) + calorie_plans (plan exists / goal_reached) + coach_subscriptions (tier/interval/status/trial_end/cancel_at_period_end) + per-coach linked-client counts. Prices: coach 19/39/99, athlete 4.99/6.99; caps 10/25/inf. LIVE-NOW tiles: Members, Coach capacity, Engagement (+ Coach revenue partial from any test subs). Revenue / Trials / At-risk render the 'live at launch' state until billing + IAP ship (T096). Exclude is_superuser rows from the roster. NEXT: finish build -> verify vs real roster (12 users, 1 coached client, Test Coach) -> deploy -> flip to Done. Coach portal mirror of this design = separate follow-up (coach view is intentionally narrower). === DONE 2026-06-08: built + deployed (live index-DY9ie8nc.js, hash-verified). Verified vs real data via MCP: roster ~12, coaches 1 (Test Coach has NO sub -> grey LED + 'No subscription' pill + '1 client'), athletes ~11, my-clients 1, engagement computes (motaz green: weigh-in 1d / workout 2d / food 4/14), coach_subscriptions table is EMPTY + self-paying athletes=1 so Coach/Athlete revenue + Trials + At-risk correctly render the 'live at launch' placeholder (gated by BILLING_LIVE=false -- flip to true when billing + athlete IAP ship). Info-on-hover (InfoTip) on every tile; Customize button opens a show/hide panel (hidden set persisted to localStorage 'myrx_admin_hidden_tiles', default all-on) with the same info beside each toggle. Roster excludes is_superuser; rows are alphabetical A->Z; athlete rows = LED(weigh-in+workout 5d)+pills+food X/14+goal bar (NO streak -> T117 v2); coach rows = sub-health LED + tier/trial/lapsed/capacity pills + mini roster-health line.",
     "web/src/pages/admin/AdminDashboard.jsx (+ tile show/hide pref in localStorage)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T117", "Athlete weigh-in streak counter (consecutive weeks with a weigh-in)", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Deferred",
     "Split out of T116 by the user (2026-06-08) and PUSHED TO v2 -- the first item tagged to a later release than the current run (drove adding the Version column to this pipeline). It was part of the My-Clients athlete-row design (a 'streak' line tied to weigh-ins, replacing the old training-streak), but the user deferred building it. So v1's athlete row shows last-active + food X/14 only, no streak.",
     "DEFERRED to v2. When built: compute consecutive WEEKS each athlete has logged >=1 weigh-in (mirror the existing computeWeekStreak logic but off the bodyweight table), show it as a 'N-wk weigh-in streak' line on the athlete row in the admin command center. Consider mirroring to the coach portal + the client app if useful.",
     "web/src/pages/admin/AdminDashboard.jsx (athlete row stats line)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T118", "Fix: admin command-center coach tiles read the wrong (empty) source", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (QA): the new command-center 'Trials' tile showed 0 while the coach portal showed Test Coach on a 1-day-left Elite trial. Verify-first via SQL CONFIRMED the bug: the coach portal (CoachDashboard.jsx) reads trial/sub state from profiles.coach_subscription_status / coach_subscription_tier / coach_trial_ends_at, but my AdminDashboard tiles read the coach_subscriptions TABLE -- which is EMPTY (the Stripe webhook writes the profiles fields, not that table; it's unused). So the coach tiles were reading a dead source. Also my BILLING_LIVE=false gate was too broad: COACH subscriptions ARE live (Test Coach really is trialing via Stripe) -- only ATHLETE revenue (IAP) is unbuilt.",
     "DONE + deployed (live index-KinGIfA4.js). Re-sourced all coach tiles to profiles.coach_subscription_* (added the 3 fields to the profiles select; dropped the coach_subscriptions query + the sub map; coach LED/pills/tier/trial/lapsed now read profiles; coachMrr dropped the interval arg since profiles carries no interval -> monthly price). Split the gate: Total MRR / Coach revenue / Trials / At-risk are now LIVE (live:true), only Athlete revenue stays dormant via the renamed ATHLETE_IAP_LIVE=false. Net: Trials now shows 1 (Test Coach, elite, trial ends tomorrow -> also 'ending soon'), Coach revenue $0 (a trial isn't paying), matching the coach portal. VERIFIED vs DB: coach_subscriptions empty, Test Coach profiles row = trialing/elite/2026-06-09.",
     "web/src/pages/admin/AdminDashboard.jsx",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T119", "Coach client-detail mirror — reflect the finished admin view into CoachClientDetail (T079 final batch)", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08: 'do it all' -- build the long-deferred coach-reflection batch (T079's last milestone) so the coach's /coach/client/:id view mirrors the now-complete admin client-detail view. Pre-reqs handled: T095 RLS (sleep_sessions coach policy added). DONE THIS PASS + deployed (live index--27q6k3o.js, CoachClientDetail-BvNylxwf.js): (1) Dashboard tab -- replaced the 4 'snapshot coming soon' placeholder cards with the SAME 6 domain blocks the admin has (DashboardEfforts/Bodyweight/Heart/Calories/Sleep/Hydration), nav order, tier-gated (CoreRX: Bodyweight+Calories; FullRX: +Heart/Sleep/Hydration), passing the coach's `client` as the profile prop. (2) Added Heart / Sleep / Hydration tabs (reuse AdminUserHeart/Sleep/Hydration with userId+profile). (3) Upgraded Calories from the bespoke macro-only tab to the full AdminUserCalories mirror (Overview dashboard + Food Log + Macro Plan, savedBy=coach). Tabs now: Dashboard/Efforts/Bodyweight/Heart/Calories/Sleep/Hydration. Coach gates kept (no Suspend/Delete/Settings/Billing/Timeline; Message + Manage-macros header toggle stay). Removed now-dead imports (MacroPlanEditor/Sparkles/Info/Scale).",
     "FOLLOW-UP PASS (same day, 'do everything before moving on to next' -- deployed live index-7KmuKy_9.js): (a) DONE -- basePath/effort-routing wired end to end. Threaded basePath through AdminUserActivity (default '/admin/user' so admin is untouched) + DashboardEffortsBlock now receives basePath='/coach/client' from CoachClientDetail; added coach effort routes in App.jsx (/coach/client/:userId/effort/cardio/:slug -> CoachCardioDetailRoute placed BEFORE the generic, + /coach/client/:userId/effort/:kind/:slug -> CoachEffortDetailRoute); AdminEffortDetail + AdminCardioDetail now derive detailBase from the URL (routePath.startsWith('/coach/') ? '/coach/client' : '/admin/user') so their back-links return to the correct portal's ?tab=activity. Coach efforts now open + return inside /coach/... with no /admin 404 leak (verified the two coach routes shipped in the live bundle). STILL DEFERRED (deliberate, NOT regressions): (b) Calories macro-edit gate -- AdminUserCalories stays always-editable for the coach regardless of macros_managed_by_coach (faithful-mirror choice; revisit if that toggle should gate editing). (c) coach activity-log labeling. (d) VISUAL QA needs a coach login (can't be done from here -- user to eyeball the coach portal).",
     "web/src/pages/coach/CoachClientDetail.jsx; (remaining) AdminUserActivity.jsx + AdminEffortDetail/AdminCardioDetail + App.jsx coach routes",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T120", "Unlink an account from a coach's roster (coach-initiated)", "Coach/Admin", "Web+DB", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 ('when done, we need to work on the mechanic of unlinking an account from coach's roster'), viewing the coach portal. FINDING: the ADMIN already had a full coach-management mechanic (AthleteCoachingChip on AdminUserDetail -> admin_set_athlete_coaching RPC can detach a coach with a type-SWITCH gate). The real gap was a COACH-INITIATED unlink -- the coach portal had NO remove affordance (CoachClients is a pure roster list; CoachClientDetail header only had Message + Manage-macros, with removal explicitly admin-only). Built the coach side. Design calls (one-at-a-time, all answered by user): (1) PLACEMENT = client detail page (CoachClientDetail header), not a roster-row button. (2) ACCESS DROP = immediate -- athlete falls back to their own b2c tier via resolveTier the moment coach_id->null; reuse the existing banner + pick-a-plan story, same end-state as the admin detach. (3) CONFIRMATION = type-REMOVE gate (mirrors admin's type-SWITCH). (4) MACRO PLAN = keep the targets, flip macros_managed_by_coach->false so the athlete inherits + can edit (calorie_plans numbers untouched).",
     "DONE + deployed (live index-DDgGdY8u.js; CoachClientDetail-oGLaA6Mo.js verified to contain coach_remove_athlete). DB: migration coach_remove_athlete_v1 -- SECURITY DEFINER RPC, ownership-gated (caller must = target.coach_id; SECURITY DEFINER bypasses RLS so this check IS the access control), nulls coach_id + flips macros_managed_by_coach off + logs a coach:detached activity_event; relies on existing profiles triggers (trg_clear_coach_ack -> nulls coach_change_acknowledged_at -> fires the athlete's banner; trg_sync_is_self_coached -> is_self_coached=true). b2c_subscription_tier untouched (immediate fall-back, no silent change). WEB: CoachClientDetail header gets a destructive 'Remove' pill -> RemoveFromRosterModal (type REMOVE) -> rpc('coach_remove_athlete') -> navigate('/coach/clients'). CONSISTENCY FIX (paired migration admin_set_athlete_coaching_clear_macro_flag_on_self): the admin detach-to-self path now ALSO clears macros_managed_by_coach -- it previously orphaned the flag, locking a detached athlete out of editing their own macros. ATHLETE REFLECTION = no new build: mobile CoachChangeBanner already renders the 'You're now self-managed' lost-coach variant on coach_id->null (previously_had_coach stays true), and mobile resolveTier + the realtime profile sub lock FullRX features live -- identical to the admin detach. Coach client-count/cap is derived (count of coach_id=coach.id) so removal frees a seat automatically; no explicit decrement. DEFERRED: visual coach-portal QA needs a coach login (user to eyeball); optional 'removed' roster toast skipped (the athlete vanishing from the roster is the confirmation); re-invite is the existing CoachInvite flow (athlete re-accepts).",
     "supabase: coach_remove_athlete_v1 + admin_set_athlete_coaching_clear_macro_flag_on_self migrations; web/src/pages/coach/CoachClientDetail.jsx (Remove pill + RemoveFromRosterModal + handleRemove + useLocation nav)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T121", "Single-point charts — render the lone data point (web admin + coach)", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08, viewing a coach client with a single weigh-in: 'something bugs me about seeing an empty graph when only one point of data is in there, why cant we show the 1 point like mobile does it ... this needs to be across all graphs on both admin and coach.' Recharts line charts were gated on length >= 2, so a single logged point rendered an EMPTY graph. Mobile already shows single points (centered dot). Fix = render the lone point everywhere, matching mobile + the two web surfaces that already did it right (AdminUserActivity duplicates the point to a flat 2-pt line; AdminStrengthRepsOnlyDetail already gated at >= 1).",
     "DONE + deployed (live index-D96NtJRG.js). Relaxed every chart-render gate from >= 2 to >= 1 so a single point renders: 15 strength/cardio detail mirrors + AdminEffortDetail via a verified codemod (asserted each pattern was unique before replacing, 16 edited / 0 skipped), DashboardBodyweightBlock (gate + dot={false} -> conditional single-point dot {r:4}), AdminUserBody (BodyweightChart < 2 return guard -> < 1, plus its render gate). Every one of these <Line>s already carried dot={{r:3}}, and the Y-domains use multiplicative (minV*0.9 / maxV*1.1, *0.85/*1.15), `|| 1`, or 'auto' padding -> a lone point lands vertically CENTERED; the category XAxis centers it horizontally. PB reference lines stay gated on > 1 (no personal-best line from one point -- matches mobile's data.length <= 1 rule). Verified ALREADY-correct + left untouched: AdminUserActivity (point-duplication), AdminStrengthRepsOnlyDetail (>= 1), HrZoneChart (n===1 centers, used by Heart dashboard+tab), SleepConsistencyChart (renders a bar), CalorieTrendGraph (bar + dot), Hydration BarChart (single bar). COACH PORTAL inherits all fixes automatically -- it reuses the admin/shared chart components (CoachClientDetail Dashboard blocks + the admin detail mirrors via basePath). DEFERRED: visual QA (user to eyeball; can't from here).",
     "codemod across web/src/pages/admin/detail/AdminStrength{Assisted,Bodyweight,Ballistic,Carry,Isometric,Leverage,Load,Weighted,Olympic}Detail.jsx + AdminCardio{BeatYourBest,AirBike,Rucking,Pace,Swimming,StairMill}Detail.jsx + admin/AdminEffortDetail.jsx; web/src/components/DashboardBodyweightBlock.jsx; web/src/pages/admin/tabs/AdminUserBody.jsx",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T122", "Admin settings review — follow-ups (coach About dedup + admin Macro Plan verify)", "Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 reviewed the admin's own settings page (/admin/profile -> Settings tab = the shared AccountSettings 4-section panel; + a Macro Plan tab). Decisions: (1)+(2) keep Delete-account + Billing OFF for the admin (platform owner -- no self-delete, no subscription). (3) dedup the COACH's About (it showed up TWICE -- a standalone top-level tab AND the AccountSettings About sub-tab). (5) keep the admin Macro Plan tab but verify it is wired to the admin's own account.",
     "DONE + deployed. (3) Removed the coach's standalone top-level About tab in CoachProfile (TABS entry + render block + COACH_ABOUT_LEGAL_LINKS const + now-unused ChevronRight import) + added a stale-tab guard so a persisted 'about' tab falls back to Settings. About now lives in ONE place for BOTH coach and admin: the Settings tab's About sub-section (AccountSettings AboutTab), which already renders the coach docs via its is_coach/superuser gate -- a superset of the 9 docs the top-level had, so nothing is lost. Preserved the 'operated by Northern Princess LLC, Michigan, USA' required disclosure by adding it to the shared AboutTab. (5) VERIFIED the admin Macro Plan is correctly wired: AdminProfile loads calorie_plans WHERE user_id = the admin's own id, and MacroPlanEditor saves payload.user_id = user.id with no target/savedBy override on the self path -> reads + writes the admin's own plan with self-attribution. No code change needed. The open question of whether the ADMIN should keep an About section at all (#3 admin half) is folded into T123 (Legal repo).",
     "web/src/pages/coach/CoachProfile.jsx; web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx (AboutTab disclosure line)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T123", "Legal repo -- searchable legal-doc viewer as a 'Legal' tab in the admin Libraries page", "Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (admin-settings review #4): 'make this page more of our legal repo ... give it capacity to search the docs, show clauses with keywords searched.' PLACEMENT CHANGED 2026-06-09: user moved it OFF the About page -> 'shift it to be in the library page, a new tab called legal.' Confirmed: read + search ONLY (no editing -- the docs are code), cross-doc keyword search with clause snippets + highlight + jump-to-section.",
     "DONE + deployed (web live index-Dz-T84z2.js). Added a 'Legal' tab to /admin/libraries (next to Movements + Foods, ?tab=legal). SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH: gave LegalLayout an EMBEDDED mode via a new LegalEmbedContext -- when a doc renders inside the provider it emits a compact title + a <div data-legal-prose> body, no public-page chrome; the public /terms,/privacy,... routes don't provide the context so they render UNCHANGED (legal doc files untouched). AdminLegalLibrary.jsx: renders all 9 docs hidden once in embed mode, extracts a cross-doc index from the rendered DOM (each <h2> -> section heading + body text scoped to [data-legal-prose]), then: empty query -> doc list (title + section count); query -> grouped result rows with ~70-char clause snippets, keyword highlighted; clicking a result opens the doc in a reading pane (re-rendered embedded, keyed to remount clean), wraps query matches in <mark> via a TreeWalker text-node highlighter (skips MARK/SCRIPT/STYLE/BUTTON), and smooth-scrolls to the matching <h2>. 9 docs: Terms, Privacy, Cookie, Acceptable Use, Coach Agreement, Refund, Health & Medical Disclaimer, DPA, How We Compute. Admin-only (chunk grew ~600kB, lazy admin route -- acceptable). Minor: inline cross-links inside a doc navigate to the public route (v2 could intercept); re-clicking a different clause in an already-open doc doesn't re-scroll (key unchanged).",
     "web/src/pages/legal/LegalLayout.jsx (embed mode + LegalEmbedContext + data-legal-prose); web/src/pages/admin/AdminLegalLibrary.jsx (new); web/src/pages/admin/AdminLibraries.jsx (Legal tab)",
     "2026-06-09"),

    ("T124", "Platform-level admin settings (global config, not personal account)", "Admin", "Web+DB", "Open",
     "User 2026-06-08 (admin-settings review #6): liked the idea of a platform-wide admin settings surface, distinct from the admin's PERSONAL account page. Net-new -- never discussed before this review. Candidate levers: defaults for new accounts, feature flags / global toggles, notification rules (email the admin on new signups / new messages / coach lapses), other platform-wide config.",
     "OPEN -- deferred to v2 per user ('open a new task and defer it to v2'). Scope on its own when picked up: which global levers the admin actually needs, where it lives in the admin shell (a new nav item vs a tab on /admin/profile), and the backing store (a singleton platform_settings table, RLS superuser-only).",
     "(planned) new admin platform-settings page in the admin shell + supabase platform_settings table (superuser-only RLS)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T125", "Wearable connected/sync state bleeds across accounts on the same device (Connect tab + Heart page)", "Athlete", "Mobile", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08, TWO sightings of the SAME root bug: (1) HEART PAGE -- 'says in the bottom synced in last 22 hours but the page is not linked to anything because the account that's actually synced is a different one opened on the same device.' (2) CONNECT TAB -- on jarah.motaz@gmail.com the Connect tab showed 'Samsung Health -- Connected - last synced 23 hr ago' with a Disconnect option, but the REAL Samsung connection is on motaz.jarrah@hotmail.com (same phone). Both symptoms: the wearable connected-state + 'synced N ago' read DEVICE-scoped state instead of ACCOUNT-scoped. Account A connects on a device -> account B signed in on the same device sees A's connection + sync stamp even though B is connected to nothing.",
     "DONE (mobile -- reload to see; no web deploy). VERIFIED root cause via DB, and it was NOT lastSyncStorage (that store is HC-only): the Samsung bleed came from samsungHealth.getStatus() querying user_integrations by PLATFORM only (no user_id filter), colliding with the 'Coaches see roster integrations' RLS SELECT policy (user_id IN clients-of-auth.uid()). A coach/admin (gmail) calling getStatus therefore got their CLIENT's (hotmail's) samsung_health row back -> 'Connected · synced 23h ago' on the coach's OWN Connect tab + Heart + Sleep (all read getStatus -> samsung.connected / lastSyncedAt). DB confirmed exactly ONE samsung_health row exists (hotmail's); gmail has none -> pure RLS-roster read-through, no stale row. FIX: getStatus now fetches auth.uid() and adds .eq('user_id', userId) (returns not-connected when signed out). requestConnect + disconnect were already user-scoped and syncRecent already had a per-user bleed guard -- getStatus was the one gap. Fixes every reported symptom (Connect tab Samsung + Heart + Sleep footers). REMAINING (theoretical, NOT observed -- deferred, flagged to user): Health Connect's connected state is device-grant-based (hcConnected = hcGranted.length>0, no per-user opt-in record) and its 'last synced' uses per-device lastSyncStorage, so HC would bleed the same way on a shared device IF a user connected it. Lower stakes than the Samsung case (HC perms are app-level, not a client's private data leaked cross-account) + needs a per-user HC opt-in record to fix cleanly.",
     "mobile/src/lib/integrations/samsungHealth.ts (getStatus -> .eq('user_id', auth.uid()))",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T126", "Nonsensical 'your coach hasn't locked in a phase starting weight' on admin/coach own Calories", "Athlete/Coach/Admin", "Mobile", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 saw on their ADMIN account (mobile Calories -> 'Current weight goal' card): 'Your coach hasn't locked in a phase starting weight yet. Once they do, your progress toward 0.0 lb will appear here.' Nonsensical for an admin -- they have no coach. CONDITION (calories.tsx ~line 1439): the card hits this fallback when (!startKg || !goalKg || |startKg-goalKg| < 0.1) AND canEditPlanHere === false; the else-branch then assumes a separate human coach ('your coach hasn't locked in...'). BLAST RADIUS: canEditPlanHere is false for (a) real coached CLIENTS -- for whom the copy is CORRECT/intended; (b) ADMINS on mobile (they edit their plan only on web); (c) COACHES on mobile (they manage their own plan from web per the settings decision). So admins AND coaches whose web-set plan lacks a starting/goal weight see the wrong 'your coach hasn't...' copy + a '0.0 lb' (fromKg(goalKg ?? 0)). Same string also lives in web CalorieDashboard.jsx -- check reachability (admins/coaches normally set macros via the web Macro Plan tab, not a Calories page).",
     "DONE (mobile -- reload to see; no web deploy). VERIFIED the '0.0' root cause via DB: the admin's calorie_plan row has goal_weight_kg = NULL (they set a -20% deficit + a starting weight on the web Macro Plan tab but left the OPTIONAL goal-weight field blank), so the card's fallback fires on !goalKg and prints fromKg(goalKg ?? 0) = '0.0'. That's also why the admin shows a real 'cals target' (the deficit still yields a daily number) while the weight-goal card has nothing to show. Test Coach differed only because they have NO plan row at all -> PendingView, not the goal card. FIX (covers every role x plan-state combo, calories.tsx): (1) canEditPlanHere now excludes coaches too (isSelfCoached && !isAdmin && !isCoach) -- coaches are web-only on mobile like admins (decision #1). (2) PendingView gained a webManaged mode: staff with NO plan see 'Manage your plan on the web -> Macro Plan tab' instead of the athlete CTA (coach) or the wrong 'waiting for your coach' (admin). (3) The goal-card fallback else now splits: staff -> 'Set a goal weight in the Macro Plan tab on your web portal to track progress here'; real coached athlete -> 'Your coach hasn't set a goal weight for this phase yet. Once they do, your progress will appear here.' (4) The bogus '0.0' interpolation is GONE from both (decision #4). Self-coached athletes unchanged; staff WITH a real goal still get the normal read-only progress bar. Verified the web Macro Plan editor genuinely has a goal-weight field (optional -> saved null when blank) so 'go to web' is actionable. tsc clean. WEB CHECK (corrected -- I had wrongly called the web copy a frozen athlete page): athletes are mobile-only on web since May 27 2026 (athlete pages archived; /app -> DownloadAppPlaceholder), so NO athlete reaches any web data page. The web CalorieDashboard is the ACTIVE read-only coach/admin client-mirror (rendered by AdminUserCalories when staff open a client's Calories tab). On inspection it does NOT have this bug: the whole 'Current weight goal' card is gated on result.goalWeightKg being truthy (a client with no goal shows NO card, not a '0.0'), and its single fallback (goal set but starting weight missing/degenerate) already uses neutral copy ('No phase starting weight locked in yet...') with the REAL goal number. So T126 was mobile-only; no web change needed.",
     "mobile/app/(app)/calories.tsx (canEditPlanHere excludes coaches; PendingView webManaged mode + staff invocation; goal-card fallback staff/coached split with the 0.0 removed). NOT touched: web/src/components/CalorieDashboard.jsx (active coach/admin client-mirror -- verified it has no bug: card gated on goal, neutral copy, no 0.0)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T127", "Remove light/dark theme -- lock dark-only everywhere", "Athlete/Coach/Admin", "Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (settings curation decision #1) FIRST asked for light/dark on every surface incl. mobile, default dark. On investigation, mobile light mode proved to be an APP-WIDE refactor (62 module-level StyleSheet.create blocks across 57 files all bake the static dark palette at import time; no ThemeContext exists on mobile, so runtime switching would mean re-architecting all of them + designing a full light palette). User REVERSED the decision: 'if its that big i dont need it, remove it from everywhere instead, clean up and close this task.' So light/dark is dropped entirely -- the app is now dark-only on both web AND mobile, which is also consistent (no surface has a light toggle).",
     "DONE + deployed (live index-Bk-UlsMV.js). The ONLY light/dark switch in the whole app was the Appearance toggle in the web Settings (AccountSettings PreferencesTab, the single useTheme `toggle` consumer); removed it. ThemeContext.jsx neutralized to dark-only: the provider now just force-adds the `dark` class + clears any stale localStorage 'theme'='light' from before, and useTheme() returns { theme: 'dark' } (with a null-safe fallback) so the ~6 read-only consumers (Landing, Navbar, ForCoaches, AcceptInvite, LegalLayout, coach Signup -- they only read `theme` to pick a dark logo variant) keep working unchanged. Removed the now-dead Sun/Moon + useTheme imports from AccountSettings. MOBILE needed nothing -- it was already dark-only (no theme toggle ever existed). Residual inert bits intentionally left (harmless): the `:root`/no-.dark light CSS vars in web index.css are never applied now; the read-only useTheme consumers still call the hook (always get dark). Could be fully purged later but not worth the risk/churn.",
     "web/src/contexts/ThemeContext.jsx (locked dark); web/src/components/AccountSettings.jsx (removed Appearance toggle + Sun/Moon/useTheme imports + the useTheme() call)",
     "2026-06-08"),

    ("T128", "App-launch wearable auto-sync (Heart/Sleep fresh on open)", "Athlete", "Mobile", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-08 (alongside T125): 'why do we only sync when we load the heart or sleep page -- shouldn't we sync on app start so when i visit the pages i already see fresh data, but ALSO keep the syncs on those pages so if new fresh data appears after app load it still refreshes.' Before: sync ran ONLY on Heart/Sleep tab focus (useFocusEffect) + pull-to-refresh; there was no app-start sync (CLAUDE.md listed app-launch auto-sync as the unbuilt 'Phase 1.1').",
     "DONE (mobile -- reload to see). Added a one-shot, fire-and-forget background sync in the authed shell (app/(app)/_layout.tsx): on first mount with a signed-in user it runs samsungSyncRecent(7) + syncSleepRecent(30), ref-guarded so it fires once per app session, errors swallowed, never blocks the UI. No-ops for users with no integration row (per-account bleed guard) + on iOS (no native module). The per-page useFocusEffect syncs on Heart/Sleep STAY in place, so data still refreshes when the watch pushes new readings after launch -- exactly the both-and behaviour requested. Safe with T125: the startup sync only ever touches the signed-in user's own data.",
     "mobile/app/(app)/_layout.tsx (startup-sync useEffect + samsungHealth imports)",
     "2026-06-08"),

